<TITLE> 2 killed in Kushtia 'crossfire' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Aug 27 (bdnews24.com)Two alleged gangsters were killed in a 'gunfight' with police in Kushtia town on Wednesday night, police said. Kushtia Sadar police chief AKM Farukh Hossain told bdnews24.com early on Thursday that at 10:45pm a gang of alleged gangsters fired on a contingent of detective police patrolling East Mazampur area of the town. Reinforcement from the police station was rushed to the scene where the shooting continued for at least half an hour. The alleged criminals fled the scene in the face of heavy firing, Hossain added. Police found the bullet-riddled corpse of 'Sumon', 28. 'Sohel', 26, another alleged miscreant who was critically injured, who died when taken to hospital. Sohel was identified as the son of one 'Majnu' and Sumon as son of Kajem Mistri, residents of East Mazampur. Police recovered a gun and five rounds of ammo from the spot, the police officer said. Police claimed that both were notorious gangsters and drug peddlers. bdne
